Former finance minister Des van Rooyen testifies at the State Capture Commission of Inquiry on Tuesday afternoon. Earlier, he cross-examined former Treasury Director General Lungile Fuzile. Van Rooyen was appointed finance minister by then-president Jacob Zuma, following the shocking removal of Nhlanhla Nene. His appointment however lasted four days due to a nationwide #ZumaMustFall protest, which resulted in Zuma replacing Van Rooyen with Pravin Gordhan. 